	     Tripoli - At least 36 immigrants died and 42 are reported missing after a makeshift boat was wrecked off Libya's coast, a naval spokesperson told AFP on Sunday. Colonel Ayub Kassem said the accident took place on Tuesday. "The boat sank four kilometres off Garabulli [50km east of Tripoli]. We were able to save 52 people of various nationalities. Thirty-six bodies have been recovered so far, 24 of them today [Sunday]," he said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  